.Dd $Mdocdate$
.Dt KHTTP_FCGI_FREE 3
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm khttp_fcgi_free ,
.Nm khttp_fcgi_child_free
.Nd free a FastCGI instance for kcgi
.Sh LIBRARY
.Lb libkcgi
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In sys/types.h
.In stdarg.h
.In stddef.h
.In stdint.h
.In stdlib.h
.In kcgi.h
.Ft "enum kcgi_err"
.Fo khttp_fcgi_free
.Fa "struct kfcgi *fcgi"
.Fc
.Ft void
.Fo khttp_fcgi_child_free
.Fa "struct kfcgi *fcgi"
.Fc
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Nm khttp_fcgi_free
and
.Nm khttp_fcgi_child_free
functions free the resources of
.Fa fcgi
allocated by
.Xr khttp_fcgi_init 3 .
After calling this function,
.Fa fcgi
cannot be used.
.Pp
The
.Nm khttp_fcgi_child_free
performs the same operations as
.Nm khttp_fcgi_free ,
but is careful not to trample on any open streams.
Thus, it may be used after invoking
.Xr fork 2
without confusing the output buffer or other child processes.
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr kcgi 3 ,
.Xr khttp_fcgi_init 3
.Sh AUTHORS
The
.Nm khttp_fcgi_free
and
.Nm khttp_fcgi_child_free
functions were written by
